quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  15,91,"those who split the Qur’an into different portions."
  15,92,"By your Lord, We will surely question them all"
  15,93,"concerning what they used to do."
  15,94,"Then proclaim what you are commanded, and turn away from those who associate partners with Allah."
  15,95,"We will surely suffice you against the mockers,"
  15,96,"those who set up beside Allah another god; they will come to know."
  15,97,"We know that you are distressed by what they say."
  15,98,"So glorify your Lord with praise and be among those who prostrate [to Him],"
  15,99,"and worship your Lord until the certainty [of death] comes to you."
  16,1,"Allah’s decree is coming, so do not seek to hasten it. Glorified and Exalted is He far above what they associate with Him!"
  16,2,"He sends down the angels with revelation by His command to whom He wills of His slaves, [saying], “Warn that none has the right to be worshiped except Me, so fear Me.”"
  16,3,"He created the heavens and earth for a true purpose. Exalted is He far above what they associate with Him!"
  16,4,"He created man from a sperm-drop, and then he becomes a clear adversary."
  16,5,"And He has created the livestock for you as a source of warmth and other benefits, and from them you eat."
  16,6,"There is beauty for you in them when you bring them home to rest and when you take them out to graze."